"Release Plans" implies that there is a plan. :-). My general policy is to cut a release whenever someone asks (or within a couple of weeks of that). We've done a bunch of refactoring to the algebraic hierarchy and a few other biggish things, so I might be a bit more cautious than usual. There are also some features I'd like to see in a 0.9 that will take some time, but if you need a release I can cause one to appear.

quasiquotes is a compile time thing and you can probably exclude it from your dependencies without a problem. I'm not quite sure how they got in there.

For Commons Math: We mostly use the LP solver, some numerics routines, random number generation, and some probability distributions. Happy to accept a PR that maintains the same level of functionality with whatever version of commons math.

